  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-ON-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Full 13-factor assessment completed. Decision: Accepted. NOTE: ContextOfUse description enumerates operating ranges (temperature 37 °C ± 1 °C, inlet pressure 5–15 mmHg, outlet pressure 60–120 mmHg, flow rate 3–8 L/min, rotational speed 2000–3500 RPM, Newtonian blood viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s) in prose, but no formal hasOperatingEnvelope or hasApplicabilityConstraint is linked — the model's bounded range of valid use is therefore unspecified in machine-readable form.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-absolute-vad",
